title.narrative: AVAILABILITY OF QUALITY ECD AND FAMILY SERVICES TO CHILDREN

description.narrative: Increased availability of quality ECD & Family services to children (0-6 years) and their families, in targeted districts,which contributes to Early Childhood Development. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Young children and families, especially the most vulnerable, are utilizing quality ECD services

title.narrative: Increased availability of quality ECD & Family services to children (0-6 years) and their families, in targeted districts

description.narrative: Number of ECD spaces increased from 4,501 in 2018 to 23,191 as a result of Government programme of establishing at least two home based ECD centres in each village. A total of 758,505 children (0-6 years) received integrated ECD services of which 58,182 children (30,250 girls; 27,932 boys) received direct support from UNICEF. A total of 2,342 caregivers (1,282 females; 1,160 males) were trained to provide quality ECD services. An integrated package of ECD services across nutrition, WASH, social protection, play based early learning and child protection was implemented in 22 districts UNICEF supported districts. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:07/08/2020
